JD - 4:

Key Responsibilities
• Operate VTOL drones for testing, validation, and operational missions.
• Conduct pre-flight checks, mission planning, and post-flight analysis.
• Execute flight tests under varying conditions to assess performance and reliability.
• Record and report flight data, anomalies, and provide feedback for system improvements.
• Ensure compliance with DGCA and internal safety protocols during all operations.
• Assist in developing SOPs for VTOL drone operations.
• Support integration and troubleshooting of payloads and avionics systems.

Required Qualifications
• Minimum 3–5 years of experience in drone piloting, preferably VTOL platforms.
• DGCA Remote Pilot License (RPL) or equivalent certification.
• Strong understanding of UAV flight control systems, navigation, and mission planning software.
• Familiarity with DGCA regulations and defense operational standards.
• Ability to analyze flight data and provide technical feedback.

Preferred Qualifications
• Experience in defense/aerospace projects or military UAV operations.
• Knowledge of advanced VTOL systems and hybrid propulsion technologies.
• Background in avionics or mechanical engineering is a plus.

Key Competencies
• Precision and situational awareness during flight operations.
• Strong problem-solving and troubleshooting skills.
• Ability to work in high-pressure and dynamic environments.

