JD - 12:

What you’ll do
• Organize and label flight logs, sim logs, design logs, sensor data, and video data into structured datasets.
• Build pipelines to clean, parse, index, and query large volumes of aerospace telemetry.
• Train LLM-based models to interpret logs and generate performance metrics, summaries, and fault signatures.
• Develop internal tools for engineers to search, visualize, and analyze logs quickly.
• Work with autonomy, GNC, and flight-test teams to define which metrics and behaviors must be extracted.

What we're looking for
• Strong Python skills and experience with data processing, time-series analysis, or telemetry logs.
• Experience training or fine-tuning LLMs or ML models.
• Ability to work with large, messy, multimodal datasets.
• Clear systems thinking — able to design pipelines that make engineers faster.

